' Cross-group shared-component ledger (TM-CA-165) — two DISTINCT cosigner groups
' {A,s} and {B,s} share the component wallet Σ⟦Ground(s)⟧. The acceptance gate (and
' the replay re-verification) run a LIVE cross-group residual ledger in canonical
' SigKey order, drawing the shared wallet DOWN as each group is admitted — so the
' two groups cannot jointly over-draw it (linearity: no contraction). The pre-fix
' static per-group effective re-read the shared wallet's FULL balance per group, so
' both admitted and over-drew (un-funded compute, the deploys run unmetered).
'
' Source of truth for cost-accounting-impl/d2-9-funding-flow.md §4 and
' cost-accounting-threat-model.md TM-CA-165.
'
' Palette:  supply pools / admit / conserve mint #C8E6C9 · effectiveΣ fold teal #B2DFDB
'   decision amber #FFE082 · reject / over-draw red #EF9A9A · input orange #FFE0B2
'   LIVE-ledger draw / replay blue #BBDEFB
'
' Render:  plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/diagrams/cross-group-shared-component-ledger.puml

@startuml cross-group-shared-component-ledger
!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam ArrowColor                     #444444
skinparam ActivityBorderColor            #333333
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor        #FFFFFF
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFE082
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor     #333333
skinparam PartitionBorderColor           #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor            #FFF8E1
skinparam NoteBorderColor                #666666
title Cross-group shared-component ledger (TM-CA-165) — two cosigner sets {A,s},{B,s} share Σ⟦Ground(s)⟧

start
:two compound deploys share cosigner s\nG1 = And(Ground(A), Ground(s))\nG2 = And(Ground(B), Ground(s)); <<#FFE0B2>>
:seed the LIVE ledger  remaining := raw\nΣ⟦Ground(s)⟧ = 3 (shared) ·  Σ⟦Ground(A)⟧ = Σ⟦Ground(B)⟧ = 100\n(genesis seeds per-pubkey wallets; Σ⟦And(…)⟧ absent ⇒ 0); <<#C8E6C9>>
:process groups in canonical SigKey order; <<#B2DFDB>>

partition "Group 1 (SigKey-first)" {
  :cap = remaining[And] + min(remaining[A], remaining[s])\n    = 0 + min(100, 3) = 3; <<#B2DFDB>>
  :folded demand cost+fee = 2 ≤ 3 ⇒ ADMIT; <<#C8E6C9>>
  :draw 2 DOWN the ledger (combined-first, then matched pair)\nremaining[s] : 3 → 1    remaining[A] : 100 → 98; <<#BBDEFB>>
}

partition "Group 2 (shares s)" {
  :cap = remaining[And] + min(remaining[B], remaining[s])\n    = 0 + min(100, 1) = 1     (s is DRAWN-DOWN by G1); <<#B2DFDB>>
  if (folded demand cost+fee = 2  ≤  cap = 1 ?) then (no)
    :REJECT-BOTH on the exhausted shared stack\n(linear logic: a token is spent once); <<#EF9A9A>>
  else (yes)
    :admit; <<#C8E6C9>>
  endif
}

:admitted = {G1} ·  rejected = {G2}\nsummed draw on Σ⟦Ground(s)⟧ = 2 ≤ 3  (bounded); <<#C8E6C9>>
note right
  PRE-FIX (static per-group effective): BOTH groups
  read Σ⟦Ground(s)⟧'s FULL balance 3, BOTH admit,
  combined draw 4 > 3 ⇒ 1 un-funded compute unit
  (the deploys run unmetered-for-liveness; the
  settlement silently caps the post-state).
end note
:REPLAY re-runs the IDENTICAL ledger (margin-free, SigKey order)\n⇒ ReplayAdmissionMismatch on any over-admitted block; <<#BBDEFB>>
stop

legend left
| Color | Meaning |
| <#FFE0B2> orange | the two shared-cosigner deploys (input) |
| <#C8E6C9> mint | supply / admit / conserve |
| <#B2DFDB> teal | the effectiveΣ cap fold |
| <#BBDEFB> blue | LIVE ledger draw-down / replay |
| <#FFE082> amber | the cross-group fit decision |
| <#EF9A9A> red | reject-both on the exhausted shared stack |
endlegend
@enduml
